# Data Visualization SVG Template

## Overview

Template for quantitative data visualizations: bar charts, line charts, donut charts, and metric grids. All examples use CSS custom properties for easy brand retheming.

---

## Base SVG Structure

```svg
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 1200 800" role="img">
  <title>[Infographic Title]</title>
  <desc>[Plain-text description of the data for screen readers]</desc>

  <style>
    :root {
      --accent: #E94560;
      --secondary: #16213E;
      --bg: #FFFFFF;
      --text: #333333;
      --muted: #888888;
      --grid: #E5E5E5;
      --font: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif;
    }

    text { font-family: var(--font); }
    .title { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 700; fill: var(--secondary); }
    .subtitle { font-size: 16px; fill: var(--muted); }
    .label { font-size: 14px; fill: var(--text); }
    .value { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; fill: var(--text); }
    .axis-label { font-size: 12px; fill: var(--muted); }
    .source { font-size: 11px; fill: var(--muted); }
  </style>

  <!-- Background -->
  <rect width="1200" height="800" fill="var(--bg)" />

  <!-- Title Area (top 100px) -->
  <text x="60" y="50" class="title">[Key Insight as Title]</text>
  <text x="60" y="75" class="subtitle">[Context: date range, sample size, etc.]</text>

  <!-- Chart Area (y: 120 to 700) -->
  <!-- Charts go here -->

  <!-- Source (bottom) -->
  <text x="60" y="780" class="source">Source: [data source] | [date]</text>

  <!-- Brand Logo (bottom-right) -->
  <g transform="translate(1100, 740)" opacity="0.5">
    <!-- logo-mark SVG contents -->
  </g>
</svg>
```

