## Donut Chart

```svg
<!-- Donut chart centered at (600, 400), radius 200, hole radius 120 -->
<g transform="translate(600, 400)">
  <!-- Segment 1: 45% (162 degrees) -->
  <path d="M 0,-200 A 200,200 0 0,1 190.2,61.8 L 114.1,37.1 A 120,120 0 0,0 0,-120 Z"
        fill="var(--accent)" />

  <!-- Segment 2: 30% (108 degrees) -->
  <path d="M 190.2,61.8 A 200,200 0 0,1 -100,173.2 L -60,103.9 A 120,120 0 0,0 114.1,37.1 Z"
        fill="var(--secondary)" />

  <!-- Segment 3: 25% (90 degrees) -->
  <path d="M -100,173.2 A 200,200 0 0,1 0,-200 L 0,-120 A 120,120 0 0,0 -60,103.9 Z"
        fill="var(--muted)" />

  <!-- Center label -->
  <text x="0" y="-10" class="title" text-anchor="middle" font-size="36">[Total]</text>
  <text x="0" y="20" class="subtitle" text-anchor="middle">[unit]</text>
</g>

<!-- Legend (right side) -->
<rect x="850" y="300" width="16" height="16" fill="var(--accent)" rx="2" />
<text x="875" y="313" class="label">[Segment 1] - 45%</text>

<rect x="850" y="330" width="16" height="16" fill="var(--secondary)" rx="2" />
<text x="875" y="343" class="label">[Segment 2] - 30%</text>

<rect x="850" y="360" width="16" height="16" fill="var(--muted)" rx="2" />
<text x="875" y="373" class="label">[Segment 3] - 25%</text>
```

**Note**: Donut chart paths are complex. Calculate arc endpoints based on actual data percentages. Use the SVG arc command (`A`) with correct start/end points.

