## Metric Grid (Multiple Stats)

For showing 3-4 key metrics in a row:

```svg
<!-- Metric 1 -->
<g transform="translate(150, 300)">
  <text x="0" y="0" font-size="56" font-weight="700" fill="var(--accent)"
        font-family="var(--font)">47%</text>
  <text x="0" y="35" class="label">Revenue Growth</text>
  <text x="0" y="55" class="axis-label">up from 32% last quarter</text>
</g>

<!-- Metric 2 -->
<g transform="translate(450, 300)">
  <text x="0" y="0" font-size="56" font-weight="700" fill="var(--accent)"
        font-family="var(--font)">2.4M</text>
  <text x="0" y="35" class="label">Active Users</text>
  <text x="0" y="55" class="axis-label">+18% month over month</text>
</g>

<!-- Metric 3 -->
<g transform="translate(750, 300)">
  <text x="0" y="0" font-size="56" font-weight="700" fill="var(--accent)"
        font-family="var(--font)">99.9%</text>
  <text x="0" y="35" class="label">Uptime</text>
  <text x="0" y="55" class="axis-label">last 90 days</text>
</g>
```

---

## Guidance

- Replace all bracketed `[placeholders]` with real data.
- Adjust viewBox dimensions for the target context (1080x1080 for social, 1200x800 for blog).
- Update CSS custom properties in the `<style>` block to match brand colors.
- Always include a `<title>` and `<desc>` for accessibility.
- Annotate data directly on the chart when possible -- reduce reliance on legends.
